The paper focuses on improving the performance of learning to rank (LTR) using visual features extracted from webpages. This task falls under the information retrieval (IR) domain, which is covered by the cs.IR sub-category. Additionally, the paper utilizes state-of-the-art visual feature extraction methods, such as transfer learning from pre-trained image classification models and synthetic saliency heat maps, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and multimedia (MM) research. The paper also mentions the use of non-visual features and relevance judgments, which are relevant to natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) research, covered by the cs.CL and cs.LG sub-categories, respectively.
